title: Parkland girls soccer team shuts out Whitehall
text:
Complete Box Score » 
Parkland 5, Whitehall 0 — Rapid Recap 
Parkland girls soccer team exploded for five second-half goals to break open a tight game and clinch a 5-0 victory over Whitehall on Wednesday night at Lehigh County Sports Fields. 
Turning point : Following a handball in the penalty box, senior defender Jenn Guetzlaff scored on a penalty kick with 21:21 remaining in regulation to give Parkland a 1-0 lead. The Trojans then added four more goals in the next 16 minutes to clinch the emphatic win on Senior Night. 
Top performer: Sophomore forward Brooke Schutter tallied a goal and two assists for the Trojans. Her goal came on a pass from junior midfielder Rachel Medlar and made it 4-0 with 10:48 left. Honorable mention goes to senior goalkeeper Regan Allsop , who had three saves to secure another shutout for the Trojans. 
What it means : Parkland prepares for the postseason with another impressive win over Whitehall. The Trojans also had a 5-0 win over Whitehall on Sept. 30. Parkland finishes the regular season with a 16-0 record in the Eastern Pennsylvania Conference and will be the top seed in the conference tournament, which starts on Saturday. The Trojans only allowed one goal (4-1 win over Nazareth on Sept. 12) in conference play this season.
